				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Lovely sense of the obsessive private world of an unhinged stalker &#8211; the self-justifications and entirely narcissistic viewpoint ring very true, and are both sad and disturbing. The build-up to the broken-off response to the actual physical contact is very powerful. I&#8217;m not sure if I&#8217;m being end-of-week obtuse, though, I&#8217;m not sure how you got to this from the theme &#8211; ghost of what, or whom? The speaker is the ghost in the actor&#8217;s life? It doesn&#8217;t quite gel for me, but as I say, I may be missing something obvious. But I enjoyed this, thank you.</p>
